    <string name="onboard_1_title">Memories, in the photo itself</string>
    <string name="onboard_1_body">Add a note or your voice to a photo. Engram writes it into the file, so it travels wherever the photo goes.</string>
    <string name="onboard_2_title">Yours, always</string>
    <string name="onboard_2_body">No account, no cloud, nothing leaves your phone unless you share it. The file is the memory.</string>
    <string name="onboard_honesty_title">One honest limit</string>
    <string name="onboard_honesty_body">Backups and original-quality cloud keep your memories. But most messengers and social apps recompress photos and strip them out. Share the file itself to keep the memory attached, and use the verifier to check any backup.</string>
